> Dear all=2C
>=20
> Is the notion of adjunction in 2-Cat well-understood? Here=2C 2-Cat
> stands for a 3-category the objects of which are 2-categories. I am
> mainly interested in the case where everything is strict=2C but
> comments on the non-strict cases are welcome.
>=20
> There has been a discussion recently about what should be the
> definition of fibration in an arbitrary 2-category. I do not expect
> the notion to be defined for general 3-categories=2C but is there at
> least a definition for the notion of fibration in 2-Cat?
>=20
> Many thanks in advance for your help!
>=20
> Jonathan Chiche
